Come on.

65
00:11:29,981 --> 00:11:31,608
Look for my bike shorts.

66
00:11:31,783 --> 00:11:35,219
- Working on the house today?
- Yeah. Have a nice day.

67
00:11:35,387 --> 00:11:38,754
- Please make a skylight.
- Goodbye, guys.

68
00:11:39,524 --> 00:11:42,254
- Bye-bye, guys.
- Bye, Mum.

69
00:11:42,427 --> 00:11:46,193
- I'll be right back.
- That wasn't too bad.

70
00:11:46,364 --> 00:11:48,491
Pretty day.

71
00:11:51,970 --> 00:11:55,167
- Did you forget something?
- Why?

72
00:11:55,340 --> 00:11:57,968
- Did you?
- No.

73
00:11:58,710 --> 00:12:03,113
...but the dad might open
a Chinese restaurant.

74
00:12:03,281 --> 00:12:07,581
We've skimmed this chapter,
now let's have some questions.

75
00:12:08,420 --> 00:12:11,218
- Emily?
- Does Fudge's family want...?

76
00:12:11,389 --> 00:12:15,257
- I love the Indian. He's so great.
- Why?

77
00:12:20,398 --> 00:12:22,764
Hurry, Mum. Open the door.

78
00:12:22,934 --> 00:12:25,300
You must be getting hungry.

79
00:12:26,538 --> 00:12:28,005
We're home!

80
00:13:14,619 --> 00:13:18,749
- I think your mealy worms are dead.
- They're in the pupa stage.

81
00:13:18,924 --> 00:13:22,985
I've seen the pupa stage.
These suckers are dead.

82
00:13:23,161 --> 00:13:28,030
- Honey, you can start them again.
- I'm sick. I'm tired.

83
00:13:29,434 --> 00:13:30,731
Come on.

84
00:13:45,951 --> 00:13:48,511
- I'm heading up now.
- Gili going up?

85
00:13:48,687 --> 00:13:51,247
- He's looking for his Walkman.
- OK.

86
00:13:56,661 --> 00:13:59,323
How do you feeI about skylights?

87
00:14:59,424 --> 00:15:02,154
I won't hurt you.

88
00:15:02,327 --> 00:15:05,125
- This is magic?
- I guess.

89
00:15:06,731 --> 00:15:09,063
I think you are a dream.

90
00:15:11,836 --> 00:15:16,933
- Are you a reaI Indian?
- I am Onondaga gah.

91
00:15:17,108 --> 00:15:19,508
Wolf Clan. Iroquois.

92
00:15:19,678 --> 00:15:22,442
Iroquois? I've heard of them.

93
00:15:25,784 --> 00:15:27,911
Were you always this small?

94
00:15:28,987 --> 00:15:31,956
I am not small. You are big!

95
00:15:32,123 --> 00:15:35,024
But I'm not big. You're so small.

96
00:15:39,664 --> 00:15:44,260
- Can you be the Peacemaker?
- I'm a boy. My name is Omri.

97
00:15:45,637 --> 00:15:49,368
- The Great Spirit can be a child?
- Who are you?

98
00:15:52,210 --> 00:15:54,974
Ohkwahe. Little Bear.

99
00:15:55,814 --> 00:15:57,406
Little Bear.

100
00:16:15,200 --> 00:16:19,466
- How do you know English?
- We know the English.

101
00:16:19,637 --> 00:16:21,662
They sent for us
to fight the French for them.

102
00:16:21,840 --> 00:16:24,570
When? What year?

103
00:16:25,610 --> 00:16:29,910
- Year 1761.
- 1761?

104
00:16:34,552 --> 00:16:36,884
Will you come out, Little Bear?

105
00:17:14,125 --> 00:17:16,889
You are so reaI!

106
00:17:18,329 --> 00:17:22,527
I am. Yes. Are you?

107
00:17:41,152 --> 00:17:45,612
If it is magic... the magic
will take me home. I shall go now.

108
00:17:47,826 --> 00:17:50,454
But you just got here.

109
00:17:50,628 --> 00:17:53,324
Look. This is for you.

110
00:17:58,603 --> 00:18:02,300
- What is it?
- It's a tepee. You know, a tepee.

111
00:18:02,474 --> 00:18:04,704
I do not know.

112
00:18:08,246 --> 00:18:10,771
- Terrible.
- It's plastic.

113
00:18:10,949 --> 00:18:14,908
Plaz-teck... Plazteck.

114
00:18:17,455 --> 00:18:20,117
- Terrible.
- I want to try. Wait.

115
00:18:36,140 --> 00:18:38,040
You can sleep here.

116
00:18:43,815 --> 00:18:47,615
You and I, we are together? Here?

117
00:18:47,785 --> 00:18:51,448
We are here... together.

118
00:18:55,994 --> 00:18:58,258
It's weird for me, too.

119
00:18:58,429 --> 00:19:01,592
- Do you make it night now?
- It is night.

120
00:19:02,634 --> 00:19:05,159
Yes, it is night.

121
00:19:08,840 --> 00:19:14,278
- I will be with you when the sun rises?
- I hope. Go to sleep now.

122
00:19:17,749 --> 00:19:19,216
Sleep?

123
00:19:21,619 --> 00:19:23,985
- You sleep?
- Yes.

124
00:19:37,969 --> 00:19:39,937
It is magic.

125
00:20:30,521 --> 00:20:32,216
Halt!

126
00:21:13,965 --> 00:21:17,662
Great Omri... up.

127
00:21:18,836 --> 00:21:20,531
A new day.

128
00:21:24,175 --> 00:21:26,302
The day came without you.

129
00:21:27,345 --> 00:21:31,645
Do you make more magic now?
Plazteck things?

130
00:21:31,816 --> 00:21:34,876
- Make what?
- A white man's gun.

131
00:21:35,053 --> 00:21:37,886
No way. What else?

132
00:21:39,357 --> 00:21:41,689
Make King George.
I would like to see him.

133
00:21:41,859 --> 00:21:44,521
I don't have any kings.

134
00:21:45,563 --> 00:21:48,555
Where is your fire?
How does your wife cook?

135
00:21:48,733 --> 00:21:51,702
We're inside. We can't have a fire.

136
00:21:51,869 --> 00:21:55,327
I don't have a wife.
Do you have a wife?

137
00:21:55,506 --> 00:21:58,407
- She died.
- I'm sorry.

138
00:22:08,453 --> 00:22:10,978
I have decided to stay.

139
00:22:11,889 --> 00:22:14,687
- For a time.
- Really?

140
00:22:16,761 --> 00:22:19,821
- Really.
- I'll make you a bow and arrow.

141
00:22:19,997 --> 00:22:23,831
Good! Tools, also.
I shall build a longhouse.

142
00:22:24,869 --> 00:22:28,134
Onondaga gah do not sleep in tepee.

143
00:22:28,740 --> 00:22:31,368
What's a longhouse?

144
00:22:39,517 --> 00:22:43,044
The mother's house. The clan home.
It is made of wood. Very strong.

145
00:22:43,221 --> 00:22:47,021
I can find tools. How about a horse?
I can make you a horse.

146
00:22:47,191 --> 00:22:49,853
- A horse?
- To ride.

147
00:22:50,027 --> 00:22:51,995
Iroquois walk.

148
00:23:01,205 --> 00:23:03,070
What is that?

149
00:23:05,676 --> 00:23:06,904
Outside.

150
00:23:08,646 --> 00:23:10,443
Take us outside, Earth Grasper.

151
00:23:41,512 --> 00:23:44,709
Don't run away. Please.

152
00:24:26,958 --> 00:24:29,791
This is the same as where I live.

153
00:24:34,665 --> 00:24:37,532
We'd better go. Get in. Get in.

154
00:25:05,496 --> 00:25:07,327
Get out! No!

155
00:25:48,306 --> 00:25:51,673
- I need bigger weapons.
- You're hurt.

156
00:25:51,842 --> 00:25:55,334
Not much. I need husks.

157
00:25:55,513 --> 00:25:58,209
Tie it tight. Stops the bleeding.

158
00:26:08,793 --> 00:26:11,227
Husks... Where are the husks?

159
00:26:11,395 --> 00:26:13,795
What are husks?

160
00:27:17,795 --> 00:27:19,990
Don't be afraid. It's all right.

161
00:27:20,164 --> 00:27:22,826
I'm a dream you're having.
Someone's hurt.

162
00:27:33,444 --> 00:27:36,242
Hurt? Someone?
Well, I'm your man, then.

163
00:27:37,381 --> 00:27:40,475
No, let me have a look.
I can do this in my sleep, mate.

164
00:27:40,651 --> 00:27:44,018
- Is he hurt bad?
- Dream, is it?

165
00:27:44,188 --> 00:27:46,679
I should have guessed.
Am I asleep? What?

166
00:27:46,857 --> 00:27:51,351
The whole rotten war's a nightmare.
No, it's not bad. We'll tape him up.

167
00:27:51,529 --> 00:27:55,295
I'll be jiggered! A bloomin' Injun.

168
00:27:58,002 --> 00:28:00,664
Englishman... Healer?

169
00:28:03,007 --> 00:28:08,206
Me? Well, I never heard it
put that way. Yes, I am.

170
00:28:08,379 --> 00:28:11,348
- I'm a healer.
- You are, are you?

171
00:28:11,515 --> 00:28:15,576
Well, that's something
we've got in common then, isn't it?

172
00:28:16,554 --> 00:28:21,218
Yes. This is not much.
Do you have husks?

173
00:28:21,392 --> 00:28:23,826
A bloomin' Injun!

174
00:28:24,395 --> 00:28:26,488
A right rum dream this is.

175
00:28:26,664 --> 00:28:31,465
I feeI like I'm really in this dream.
Very reaI, very clear. Exciting.

176
00:28:31,635 --> 00:28:34,763
So... Custer's last stand, was it?

177
00:28:34,939 --> 00:28:37,237
I know a bit, you know,
read up as a boy.

178
00:28:37,408 --> 00:28:40,400
- You Sitting Bull.
- No.

179
00:28:42,780 --> 00:28:44,179
How!

180
00:28:46,450 --> 00:28:47,815
How!

181
00:28:49,854 --> 00:28:52,084
There we go. That'll do.

182
00:28:54,992 --> 00:28:57,961
- Thank you.
- Only doing my duty.

183
00:28:58,129 --> 00:29:01,064
- Would you like to wake up now?
- I never want to wake up.

184
00:29:01,232 --> 00:29:05,760
Mud, German shells, awfuI bloody
rats. They eat at wounded men.

185
00:29:05,936 --> 00:29:08,769
Still, can't desert, even in a dream!

186
00:29:10,040 --> 00:29:11,439
How.

187
00:29:17,414 --> 00:29:20,713
- Maybe you can dream us again.
- A pleasure.

188
00:29:20,885 --> 00:29:25,049
Tommy Atkins at your service.
Any night except if there's an attack.

189
00:29:25,222 --> 00:29:28,851
None of us gets any sleep then.
Got to win the damn war.

190
00:29:53,951 --> 00:29:56,943
You up already? Feeling better?

191
00:29:59,623 --> 00:30:02,387
I feeI pretty damn good.

192
00:30:04,028 --> 00:30:05,620
Really?

193
00:30:07,231 --> 00:30:09,631
Come on down and eat breakfast.

194
00:30:22,313 --> 00:30:24,338
You can build here.

195
00:30:37,528 --> 00:30:41,931
<i>- I need tools.
- Omri, come on down!</i>

196
00:30:42,099 --> 00:30:45,159
- Who is she?
- My mother.

197
00:30:45,869 --> 00:30:49,669
<i>Ah, genoha. The mother.</i>

198
00:30:51,742 --> 00:30:54,142
What would you like for breakfast?

199
00:30:58,182 --> 00:31:00,173
Granola, please.

200
00:31:00,985 --> 00:31:02,885
Have I died and gone to heaven?

201
00:31:03,053 --> 00:31:06,045
With berries
and cranberry juice, please.

202
00:31:42,126 --> 00:31:44,890
I have to go to schooI.

203
00:31:45,062 --> 00:31:49,055
- What is schooI?
- Learn things - all day.

204
00:31:49,233 --> 00:31:51,793
Good. Learn the stories
of your ancestors.

205
00:31:51,969 --> 00:31:54,665
Go. I am ready to build.

206
00:32:02,246 --> 00:32:06,410
- Need anything else?
- A hatchet.

207
00:32:10,854 --> 00:32:14,290
<i>Omri, let's go!</i>

208
00:32:15,993 --> 00:32:18,291
<i>- Gili.
- I'm coming.</i>

209
00:32:42,019 --> 00:32:44,078
I'll miss you.

210
00:32:50,227 --> 00:32:52,161
Come on, guys, let's go.

211
00:32:52,329 --> 00:32:54,889
- See you later Mum and Dad.
- Bye, guys.

212
00:32:55,065 --> 00:32:57,192
- Bye, Omri.
- Bye, Dad.

213
00:32:58,769 --> 00:33:01,761
OK. All right.
Can I get your attention, please?

214
00:33:01,939 --> 00:33:05,272
Are we ready? Shall we read?

215
00:33:05,442 --> 00:33:08,809
- Who wants to go first?
- Please! Can I do it?

216
00:33:08,979 --> 00:33:10,207
Emily?

217
00:33:10,381 --> 00:33:14,044
"The day I got Punisher,
the masterpiece of my collection. "

218
00:33:14,218 --> 00:33:16,709
"Also, I got
the first hologram card. "

219
00:33:16,887 --> 00:33:20,015
"I'm looking for
the originaI card of Wolverine. "

220
00:33:20,190 --> 00:33:23,125
Very good, Emily. Sam.

221
00:33:23,627 --> 00:33:27,154
"JFK. There was once a man
named JFK"

222
00:33:27,331 --> 00:33:30,425
"who always wanted to be good
and do what was right. "

223
00:33:30,601 --> 00:33:35,561
"JFK was elected President
of the United States in 1960."

224
00:33:35,739 --> 00:33:37,707
OK...

225
00:33:38,542 --> 00:33:40,339
Omri.

226
00:33:40,511 --> 00:33:42,979
"I have a magic cupboard
with a magic key. "

227
00:33:43,147 --> 00:33:46,639
"I put a plastic Indian
in the cupboard and he came alive. "

228
00:33:46,817 --> 00:33:49,342
"He is a reaI Iroquois man. "

229
00:33:49,520 --> 00:33:53,422
"He talks. He eats. He trusts me. "

230
00:33:55,092 --> 00:33:58,118
That's very interesting.
Good imagination.

231
00:35:27,451 --> 00:35:29,783
OK, OK, Omri.

232
00:35:52,376 --> 00:35:55,607
Your house is fantastic.

233
00:35:55,779 --> 00:35:59,510
It will do. It is agreeable.

234
00:36:00,217 --> 00:36:03,243
I learned a lot about you today.

235
00:36:03,420 --> 00:36:05,945
Good. Tonight, I will hunt for food

236
00:36:06,123 --> 00:36:10,287
and we will cook meat
and we will tell stories.

237
00:36:10,460 --> 00:36:12,121
You tell all about me.

238
00:36:13,397 --> 00:36:15,194
Little Bear?

239
00:36:24,474 --> 00:36:27,966
- Do you keep the man, Omri?
- Just the bow and arrow.

240
00:36:32,349 --> 00:36:34,283
Can I watch?

241
00:36:39,423 --> 00:36:43,382
He is Mohawk.
It is an excellent bow.

242
00:36:52,936 --> 00:36:55,029
It's all right.

243
00:36:55,205 --> 00:36:56,695
It's OK.

244
00:36:59,409 --> 00:37:02,105
No... Little Bear?

245
00:37:13,824 --> 00:37:17,760
- He is dead.
- He's dead? I killed him?

246
00:37:19,062 --> 00:37:22,361
He is old. His days are done.

