00:37:43,820 --> 00:37:47,722
- We must bury him.
- Bury him? Us? Here?

248
00:37:49,593 --> 00:37:52,721
Yes. You never had
a dead man here?

249
00:37:54,631 --> 00:37:56,496
<i>Omri!</i>

250
00:37:59,469 --> 00:38:02,370
Do people die here?

251
00:38:02,539 --> 00:38:06,635
- People die. We just don't see them.
- How do you not see them?

252
00:38:06,810 --> 00:38:09,210
<i>Come down here, please.</i>

253
00:38:12,783 --> 00:38:15,183
Can't I just send him back?

254
00:38:17,888 --> 00:38:20,448
You are afraid of him?

255
00:38:21,591 --> 00:38:23,388
A dead man?

256
00:38:28,198 --> 00:38:32,658
You are a child. Yes, send him back.

257
00:38:33,637 --> 00:38:36,128
- What if he was alone?
- Then he is alone!

258
00:38:38,809 --> 00:38:40,572
Where were you?

259
00:38:40,744 --> 00:38:44,805
Guiding my nephew through the woods
to live alone and learn to be a man.

260
00:38:44,981 --> 00:38:47,313
You should not do magic
you do not understand!

261
00:38:47,484 --> 00:38:49,509
<i>Omri, now!</i>

262
00:38:54,925 --> 00:38:56,825
Send him back.

263
00:38:58,328 --> 00:39:00,762
He would want to be back.

264
00:39:11,241 --> 00:39:13,368
Are you mad at me?

265
00:39:25,889 --> 00:39:28,221
What did you do with them?

266
00:39:31,394 --> 00:39:34,261
- I buried them.
- My saw blades? Why?

267
00:39:34,431 --> 00:39:37,559
Those are my things.
I work with them. I need them.

268
00:39:37,734 --> 00:39:40,168
What do you want me to do?

269
00:39:44,241 --> 00:39:47,438
We'll go to Yapp's and buy a set.
Come on.

270
00:39:49,913 --> 00:39:52,074
I can go alone. It's a block away.

271
00:39:52,249 --> 00:39:55,047
You don't need to go with me
like I'm a baby.

272
00:39:55,218 --> 00:39:58,483
I've been before.
You just didn't know.

273
00:40:04,995 --> 00:40:06,622
OK.

274
00:41:22,205 --> 00:41:24,503
What did you get? Let me see.

275
00:41:25,876 --> 00:41:28,640
What is this junk?
Give me the money.

276
00:41:31,414 --> 00:41:35,145
You! Come back!
You don't deserve that hair!

277
00:41:52,302 --> 00:41:57,262
Look. I got this guy
to go with your Indian.

278
00:41:57,440 --> 00:42:02,036
Patrick. Omri? Are you OK?

279
00:42:09,352 --> 00:42:11,980
Omri, are you sure you're OK?

280
00:42:34,210 --> 00:42:38,738
- This thing is incredible.
- Get your hands out of the way.

281
00:42:40,183 --> 00:42:43,414
Where do you think he got this?

282
00:42:43,586 --> 00:42:45,816
Look how small it is.

283
00:42:46,856 --> 00:42:49,825
- What are you looking at?
- This is incredible.

284
00:42:49,993 --> 00:42:52,655
How did you make this?

285
00:42:52,829 --> 00:42:55,024
Don't bring that rat in here.

286
00:42:55,198 --> 00:42:58,725
I found him in here, Beavis, and
my figures and my magnifying glass.

287
00:42:58,902 --> 00:43:02,599
- What else do you have that's mine?
- That thing was in here?

288
00:43:02,772 --> 00:43:05,138
This is great. Dad should see this.

289
00:43:05,308 --> 00:43:07,606
I want you both
to leave my room now.

290
00:43:07,777 --> 00:43:10,075
Jeez, temperamentaI.

291
00:43:38,908 --> 00:43:41,775
- You got to promise me...
- What?

292
00:43:43,146 --> 00:43:46,047
Little Bear, where are you?

293
00:43:47,751 --> 00:43:49,981
What are we looking for?

294
00:43:51,087 --> 00:43:52,645
Little Bear?

295
00:44:01,264 --> 00:44:03,789
Here!

296
00:44:08,705 --> 00:44:11,367
It's all right. You can come out.

297
00:44:12,275 --> 00:44:16,541
- I heard them and I ran.
- That was good.

298
00:44:16,713 --> 00:44:19,273
- They are enemies?
- Brothers.

299
00:44:19,449 --> 00:44:23,886
Brothers?
Those brothers took my house!

300
00:44:25,522 --> 00:44:27,752
I am in the dark here.

301
00:44:27,924 --> 00:44:30,552
Send me back. I want to go back.

302
00:44:30,727 --> 00:44:33,287
But I brought my friend to meet you.

303
00:44:33,463 --> 00:44:35,363
Patrick, Little Bear.

304
00:44:38,535 --> 00:44:41,470
Another Great Spirit?
Make another little man?

305
00:44:41,638 --> 00:44:44,072
No. No more men.

306
00:44:44,874 --> 00:44:48,241
- Little Bear, will you come out?
- No. You come in.

307
00:44:53,249 --> 00:44:57,208
- This is the plastic Indian?
- Not plastic any more.

308
00:44:58,321 --> 00:45:01,290
- How did you do that?
- The cupboard.

309
00:45:01,458 --> 00:45:03,323
Show me.

310
00:45:08,164 --> 00:45:10,325
Put a plastic thing in and lock it.

311
00:45:10,500 --> 00:45:13,628
If it's a person,
the person is alive.

312
00:45:18,775 --> 00:45:22,267
They're reaI people.
They can even be reaI dead people.

313
00:45:24,681 --> 00:45:26,376
- I want to make one.
