Step back, cow pie.

353
00:48:16,352 --> 00:48:18,252
How will you take care of him?

354
00:48:18,421 --> 00:48:21,857
<i>- Patrick, time to go.
- Coming! Let me keep him.</i>

355
00:48:30,033 --> 00:48:33,400
But it's got to stay a secret.

356
00:48:33,569 --> 00:48:37,562
Listen, let me keep him here tonight.
I have this under controI.

357
00:48:37,740 --> 00:48:41,301
- Bring him to schooI tomorrow.
- SchooI?

358
00:48:45,415 --> 00:48:48,043
Everybody's so big.

359
00:48:48,217 --> 00:48:51,015
You'll be OK. Don't cry.

360
00:48:51,187 --> 00:48:53,849
I always cry.

361
00:48:56,459 --> 00:48:59,485
The boys call me "Boo-hoo" Boone.

362
00:49:00,496 --> 00:49:03,556
<i>- I've got a soft heart.
- Patrick!</i>

363
00:49:07,036 --> 00:49:10,096
- Bring him to schooI. Promise?
- I promise.

364
00:49:11,140 --> 00:49:13,472
Don't put them together
- cowboys and Indians!

365
00:49:14,043 --> 00:49:15,533
Indians?

366
00:49:16,179 --> 00:49:19,478
Omri, don't turn him back, please?

367
00:49:20,283 --> 00:49:21,682
What Indians?

368
00:49:36,332 --> 00:49:38,300
Redskins.

369
00:49:39,035 --> 00:49:40,832
No!

370
00:49:41,003 --> 00:49:44,439
Wait! What in the...
You better put me down!

371
00:49:44,607 --> 00:49:46,700
Who do you think you are?

372
00:49:46,876 --> 00:49:50,937
I'm telling you the truth,
I'll lay you in your grave.

373
00:49:51,114 --> 00:49:53,708
I don't care how big you are.

374
00:49:56,853 --> 00:50:00,016
Kindly return to me my hat,
tenderfoot.

375
00:50:00,189 --> 00:50:03,989
You say you take no more men.
You tell blind stories.

376
00:50:10,366 --> 00:50:15,099
Watch out that savage don't
scalp you in your sleep, Injun lover.

377
00:50:16,072 --> 00:50:19,166
<i>You're not gonna shut me
up in here, are you?</i>

378
00:51:56,138 --> 00:52:00,541
Now we become reconciled...
as you start away.

379
00:52:14,490 --> 00:52:18,449
Now we become reconciled
as you start away.

380
00:53:05,708 --> 00:53:07,437
Don't you want this open?

381
00:53:07,610 --> 00:53:11,569
I'm not scared any more.
You can close it.

382
00:53:27,797 --> 00:53:31,289
- Is she in the dark?
- What do you mean?

383
00:53:31,467 --> 00:53:34,527
- Does she know of me?
- No.

384
00:53:37,039 --> 00:53:39,064
I'm alone.

385
00:53:41,711 --> 00:53:44,202
I need a wife.

386
00:54:14,377 --> 00:54:16,208
Come on and fight!

387
00:54:30,526 --> 00:54:32,221
Darlin'!

388
00:54:34,430 --> 00:54:39,732
Every time I try to...
We're supposed to be a team.

389
00:54:43,739 --> 00:54:45,502
Hey, dang!

390
00:54:47,743 --> 00:54:51,372
- What's the matter with that Injun?
- No, no, stop!

391
00:54:51,547 --> 00:54:53,378
Behave!

392
00:54:53,549 --> 00:54:57,610
He says I steaI his horse.
He shoots at me.

393
00:54:57,787 --> 00:55:01,154
If that's true, I'll squish him
like a bug. Boone, drop it!

394
00:55:01,991 --> 00:55:04,255
Well, she's my horse.

395
00:55:04,427 --> 00:55:07,453
- Drop it!
- No!

396
00:55:10,066 --> 00:55:15,026
I'm tired of being hauled off. I knew
you'd side with that stinkin' savage.

397
00:55:15,204 --> 00:55:18,173
He smells and he calls me
a dirty savage.

398
00:55:18,340 --> 00:55:21,537
I didn't call you dirty,
I called you stinkin'!

399
00:55:21,711 --> 00:55:23,906
Stop it, Boone!

400
00:55:24,080 --> 00:55:28,540
Listen to me. Boone is leaving.
You don't have to live together.

401
00:55:28,718 --> 00:55:31,881
Where can I buy coffee?
I like to start my day with coffee.

402
00:55:32,054 --> 00:55:34,648
OK, if you'll be good,
I'll make you breakfast.

403
00:55:34,824 --> 00:55:38,521
Omri cooks! Like a woman.
You are a woman.

404
00:55:38,694 --> 00:55:42,027
Please! You guys
are so old-fashioned.

405
00:55:42,198 --> 00:55:44,689
I'll have you know
I'm a civilised man.

406
00:55:44,867 --> 00:55:47,199
Unlike some!

407
00:55:47,369 --> 00:55:49,997
Where did you come from?

408
00:55:51,040 --> 00:55:53,770
I come from Texas, Mr Half-a-Brain.

409
00:55:53,943 --> 00:55:56,707
The United States of America,
comprende?

410
00:55:56,879 --> 00:55:58,642
Omri, Texas?

411
00:55:58,814 --> 00:56:00,941
- You're from Texas?
- Proud of it.

412
00:56:01,117 --> 00:56:04,109
- Where are you taking me?
- To schooI.

413
00:56:04,286 --> 00:56:07,119
- White man goes to schooI?
- That's right.

414
00:56:07,289 --> 00:56:09,655
- I go to schooI.
