need some help to get this scalp.

419
00:56:22,671 --> 00:56:25,572
Omri, send him back. Do it.

420
00:56:33,482 --> 00:56:38,317
Patrick! Come on! Come on!

421
00:56:41,924 --> 00:56:43,892
Come on!

422
00:56:53,769 --> 00:56:55,498
Bye-bye.

423
00:57:06,415 --> 00:57:07,712
You got him?

424
00:57:07,883 --> 00:57:11,284
CarefuI, he's so delicate. Come here.

425
00:57:12,321 --> 00:57:15,051
- Boone's in the front...
- Let me have him!

426
00:57:15,224 --> 00:57:17,351
I got to check on Little Bear.

427
00:57:17,526 --> 00:57:20,495
- You all right, Little Bear?
- Let me have that!

428
00:57:20,663 --> 00:57:22,995
- Come on! Give me him.
- Calm down, Patrick.

429
00:57:23,165 --> 00:57:25,292
Boys!

430
00:57:25,467 --> 00:57:27,401
SchooI, remember?

431
00:57:44,153 --> 00:57:45,552
All right, thank you,
Malcolm and George.

432
00:57:47,423 --> 00:57:50,449
All right, let's have...
Emily and Loretta.

433
00:57:58,200 --> 00:58:00,600
Loretta and I...

434
00:58:00,769 --> 00:58:04,296
Loretta and I are making a map
of the United States.

435
00:58:04,473 --> 00:58:06,737
We built it here on a piece of wood.

436
00:58:06,909 --> 00:58:09,309
We made the whole country
out of flour,

437
00:58:09,478 --> 00:58:14,347
water, salt and food colouring,
using beans for mountains,

438
00:58:14,516 --> 00:58:18,043
<i>yarn for the rivers
and rice for borders.</i>

439
00:58:18,220 --> 00:58:21,485
<i>We're making the desert
